                            <comment id="36721" author="ulsa" created="Sun, 15 Jun 2008 22:04:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have made the following changes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;PoolingContextSource.keyedObjectPool&lt;/tt&gt; is now &lt;tt&gt;protected&lt;/tt&gt;, thus enabling subclasses to access pooled contexts&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fixed a potential problem in &lt;tt&gt;AbstractRequestControlDirContextProcessor&lt;/tt&gt;, where &lt;tt&gt;preProcess&lt;/tt&gt; always added a new request control regardless of whether an instance of it already existed in the context (which is illegal in the case of &lt;tt&gt;PagedResultsControl&lt;/tt&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


