                            <comment id="39038" author="marthursson" created="Mon, 18 Aug 2008 17:46:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a &lt;tt&gt;SingleContextSource&lt;/tt&gt; as a package private inner class in &lt;tt&gt;LdapCompensatingTransactionOperationFactory&lt;/tt&gt;. Perhaps we could just extract that one and move it to &lt;tt&gt;core.support&lt;/tt&gt;. Would that solve this problem?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="40481" author="marthursson" created="Mon, 20 Oct 2008 21:48:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SingleContextSource is now public, which should be sufficient to solve this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41588" author="mariuss" created="Fri, 12 Dec 2008 02:54:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this mean that in 1.2.1 you cannot safely use paged results at all?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you disable pooling altogether, will paging work?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41611" author="ulsa" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2008 19:24:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If pooling is disabled, it will most likely not work, unless you use SingleContextSource or transactions as described &lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showpost.php?p=217915&amp;amp;postcount=4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We changed the default in 1.3 to be &quot;built-in pooling off&quot;, because previously paged results would accidentally work as long as you got the same connection back from the pool and the pool didn&apos;t time out. So, in test scenarios, it would look OK, but in the real world it wouldn&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="123551" author="rwinch" created="Fri, 5 Feb 2016 21:17:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-ldap/issues/153&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-ldap/issues/153&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
